35:18.074 --> 35:20.886
'Cause I can't shake the feeling

35:20.910 --> 35:22.096
that it's gonna happen again,

35:22.120 --> 35:24.389
that I'm gonna drop my
guard, and you're gonna...

35:24.413 --> 35:25.641
Justin, I wouldn't.

35:25.665 --> 35:27.133
It's too hard to believe you.

35:28.167 --> 35:29.978
And I don't wanna
be like my dad.

35:30.002 --> 35:31.939
I don't wanna just
screw somebody

35:31.963 --> 35:33.806
and have it not mean anything.

35:34.048 --> 35:38.445
But... I don't think

35:38.469 --> 35:41.313
I want it to mean
something with you.

35:45.601 --> 35:47.903
That's why I'm not
gonna sit there.

35:55.695 --> 35:56.829
Hey, Claud.

35:58.614 --> 36:02.168
Check it out. I scored
some more nuts.

36:04.328 --> 36:05.921
See, in my experience,

36:07.123 --> 36:09.800
when your heart's sore, the
best thing to do is eat.

36:09.876 --> 36:12.470
Like you'd know how I feel.

36:14.046 --> 36:16.182
Believe it or not, I do.

36:16.424 --> 36:18.184
No, you don't, Charlie.

36:19.510 --> 36:24.190
I might never see Enrico
again, and I miss him.

36:24.307 --> 36:26.660
Already I miss him so much.

36:26.684 --> 36:30.164
You never miss anyone. You
just leave them and move on.

36:30.188 --> 36:32.948
I mean, like Kirsten.

36:34.358 --> 36:35.419
You said you loved her,

36:35.443 --> 36:39.747
but then one day it just...
Poof, she's gone.

36:41.407 --> 36:43.334
You might never see her again.

36:43.868 --> 36:45.336
But you don't care.

36:46.204 --> 36:48.172
You've already got someone else.

36:51.250 --> 36:54.720
Man, Claudia, when did you
get so incredibly cruel?

36:55.546 --> 36:57.681
You really don't think
that I miss her?

36:58.507 --> 36:59.401
That's like saying

36:59.425 --> 37:01.519
that you think that I don't
have a heart at all.

37:01.552 --> 37:03.530
That's just such an
awful thing to say.

37:03.554 --> 37:04.907
Well, if you missed her so much,

37:04.931 --> 37:06.366
then how could you
get all wrapped up

37:06.390 --> 37:08.442
in that... Courtney lady?

37:10.728 --> 37:15.324
I don't know, okay. I...

37:17.401 --> 37:21.580
All I know is, I got to
Mexico feeling like crap.

37:21.906 --> 37:23.759
And then I met Courtney,

37:23.783 --> 37:26.511
and I wanted to be with her

37:26.535 --> 37:30.047
because suddenly being with her
was making that feeling go away.

37:31.165 --> 37:34.051
Or at least I thought
it was, anyway.

37:35.461 --> 37:36.521
I was an idiot, I guess,

37:36.545 --> 37:37.481
because it turns out

37:37.505 --> 37:40.307
you can't make feelings
go away by ignoring them.

37:40.758 --> 37:45.688
They stick around.
They come back.

37:51.602 --> 37:53.696
Not miss anyone? God!

38:02.530 --> 38:04.883
All the French stuff was
dubbed instead of subtitled,

38:04.907 --> 38:06.959
so I figured I'd get...

38:07.952 --> 38:09.295
Sarah?

38:10.121 --> 38:11.640
You were in the exact same
position when I left.

38:11.664 --> 38:13.841
Have you just been
standing there?

38:14.750 --> 38:16.302
No. I moved.

38:19.463 --> 38:21.473
I put my books on the shelf.

38:22.925 --> 38:24.778
Then I took them off.

38:24.802 --> 38:26.947
Then I put them on.
then I took them off.

38:26.971 --> 38:30.617
What's...? Is something wrong?

38:30.641 --> 38:32.109
No.

38:33.769 --> 38:36.780
No, not wrong, really.

38:38.399 --> 38:39.876
I mean, that's a good place

38:39.900 --> 38:41.044
for my books, you know.

38:41.068 --> 38:43.245
They definitely all fit there.

38:44.030 --> 38:45.414
But?

38:45.489 --> 38:47.249
But I don't know.

38:49.285 --> 38:52.379
Whenever I put them there,
it just kind of feels fake.

38:53.331 --> 38:55.841
You know, like I'm pretending
it's a home or something.

38:58.127 --> 39:00.679
I don't think this is right.

39:03.215 --> 39:05.976
'Cause this is not my home.

39:08.512 --> 39:11.158
I don't know what is.

39:11.182 --> 39:14.526
But... this isn't it.

39:15.728 --> 39:20.824
It's a home, yeah,
but it's not mine.

39:22.193 --> 39:23.661
So...

39:32.536 --> 39:34.046
I'll drive you.

39:35.706 --> 39:36.882
Okay.

39:37.375 --> 39:39.144
Decaf nonfat latte.

39:39.168 --> 39:42.564
Make it a low-fat
scone, a cranberry one.

39:42.588 --> 39:44.056
You got it.

39:48.094 --> 39:49.353
Hi.

39:50.054 --> 39:51.188
Hi.

39:53.766 --> 39:55.994
I'm surprised you're not
at the Silent Festival

39:56.018 --> 39:57.329
at the Rialto.

39:57.353 --> 40:01.208
I just came from <i>Mabel
and Fatty's Wash Day.</i>

40:01.232 --> 40:04.827
I was gonna go see <i>Fatty's
Magic Pants</i> at 9:30.

40:05.111 --> 40:06.954
I totally forgot your order.

40:07.154 --> 40:09.331
Decaf nonfat latte.

40:12.701 --> 40:15.514
Do you know how many people know
what kind of coffee I drink?

40:15.538 --> 40:17.808
One. You.

40:17.832 --> 40:18.850
Yeah, well.

40:18.874 --> 40:19.851
And how many people know

40:19.875 --> 40:21.770
about your obsession
with Fatty Arbuckle?

40:21.794 --> 40:24.680
It's not an obsession. It's
just a profound interest.

40:27.133 --> 40:29.393
Oh, what are we doing?

40:31.720 --> 40:33.355
I don't know.

40:33.472 --> 40:35.200
It's weird, isn't it?

40:35.224 --> 40:38.453
I mean, there's a lot
that's bad between us,

40:38.477 --> 40:40.455
but then there's all
this other stuff

40:40.479 --> 40:42.374
that just makes us feel
right with each other.

40:42.398 --> 40:44.908
I just can't figure out
how to make the two fit.

40:45.484 --> 40:47.587
Not by sleeping together.

40:47.611 --> 40:51.206
No. Definitely not. It
just makes it worse.

40:56.162 --> 40:59.381
<i>Fatty's Magic Pants</i> did
kind of jump out at me.

40:59.790 --> 41:04.511
Maybe I could go with you.

41:06.797 --> 41:09.641
I totally forgot. Was
that for here or to go?

41:11.385 --> 41:12.811
To go.

41:17.057 --> 41:18.650
Baby steps.

41:24.940 --> 41:26.376
Ar-eeba?

41:26.400 --> 41:28.462
No. Arriba. You
gotta roll the R's.

41:28.486 --> 41:29.379
- How?
- R-r-r-r-r-r.

41:29.403 --> 41:30.547
Errr...

41:30.571 --> 41:31.756
Just let your
tongue flap around.

41:31.780 --> 41:32.966
- Err-r-r.
- R-r-r-r-r-r-r.

41:32.990 --> 41:34.792
- I can't do it. Errrr-errr...
- Arriba!

41:35.159 --> 41:36.835
Arrrr.

41:43.209 --> 41:44.635
Hi, honey.

41:46.045 --> 41:47.763
Hi.

41:50.341 --> 41:53.185
Maybe I'll...

41:53.552 --> 41:55.479
Maybe I'll go unpack.

41:55.679 --> 41:57.022
Okay.

42:02.561 --> 42:04.289
I'm sorry. I thought
I'd be gone.

42:04.313 --> 42:05.332
No, no, no, no, no.

42:05.356 --> 42:06.907
Don't apologize.

42:12.363 --> 42:13.831
Where were you?

42:17.117 --> 42:19.670
We went... I...

42:20.246 --> 42:24.049
I took Claudia, you know, to...
To Mexico.

42:27.086 --> 42:30.357
You went? You went, anyway?

42:30.381 --> 42:32.526
She was having such a hard
time dealing with all this,

42:32.550 --> 42:34.893
and I had the tickets.

42:35.803 --> 42:39.273
I figured, you know, some
time together, just...

42:40.474 --> 42:41.868
Wow, Charlie.

42:41.892 --> 42:43.787
Don't, please. I've
hurt you so much.

42:43.811 --> 42:46.113
Please don't be hurt
about this too.

42:49.567 --> 42:51.253
This is the last box.

42:51.277 --> 42:53.171
Maybe I'll stick it in the car

42:53.195 --> 42:55.090
and come back and say
bye to the kids.

42:55.114 --> 42:56.675
- I'll take it out for you.
- No.

42:56.699 --> 42:58.009
I got it.

42:58.033 --> 43:01.086
I wasn't planning on
seeing you, anyway.

43:22.933 --> 43:24.484
I gave her these.

43:26.020 --> 43:28.113
After our first fight.

43:35.863 --> 43:37.549
Just tell her she
dropped them, okay.

43:37.573 --> 43:39.333
Okay.

